parameters: \N<Segi>I've kept you waiting, Lord Yuia. Riia.

\N<Yuia>Is this really okay...? No matter how much I think about it,
it keeps crossing my mind.

\N<Yuia>Lyuda and Zuuteruka haven't just disappeared. As long as I
am myself, I might continue to be pursued. Then, something
like this might happen again.

\N<Segi>As you said, Lord Yuia, even if something happens to a
person, they don't become someone else.

\N<Segi>However, we have overcome the past, the events at that
castle. With the help of the Princess Consort and my
parents.

\N<Segi>Just like that, we've overcome this time as well. And this
time, we did it with our own strength and feelings. Of
course, with the help of Irime and others, but we managed to
pull through on our own.

\N<Segi>That's why... I want us three to stay together from now on.
And because of what happened this time, I want to believe
that it has deepened the bond between us as a couple... as a
family.

I just lied to myself. I'm telling the biggest lie to my own
heart.

If it didn't exist, it would be better off not existing. It
wasn't pain for the sake of growth; it was just pain for the
sake of pain. That's all it was.

Still... because it happened, our bond deepened. Perhaps
believing that is the only way I can lighten the burden in
my heart right now.
